1. Default Parameters ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Default parameters allow you to assign a default value to a function parameter if no argument is provided.

Before ES6
function greet(name) {

    name = name || "Guest";

    console.log("Hello " + name);

}

greet();

Output

Hello Guest
ES6 Default Parameters
function greet(name = "Guest") {

    console.log(`Hello ${name}`);

}

greet();

Output

Hello Guest
Passing a Value
function greet(name = "Guest") {

    console.log(`Hello ${name}`);

}

greet("Priya");

Output

Hello Priya
Multiple Default Parameters
function add(a = 0, b = 0) {

    return a + b;

}

console.log(add());
console.log(add(10));
console.log(add(10, 20));

Output

0
10
30
2. Optional Chaining (?.) ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Optional chaining safely accesses nested object properties.

Without it, accessing a missing property causes an error.

Without Optional Chaining
let student = {
    name: "Priya"
};

console.log(student.address.city);

Output

TypeError:
Cannot read properties of undefined
With Optional Chaining
let student = {
    name: "Priya"
};

console.log(student.address?.city);

Output

undefined

No error is thrown.

Nested Example
let employee = {
    name: "Lokesh",
    address: {
        city: "Coimbatore"
    }
};

console.log(employee.address?.city);

Output

Coimbatore
Optional Chaining with Arrays
let colors = ["Red", "Green"];

console.log(colors?.[0]);
console.log(colors?.[5]);

Output

Red
undefined
Optional Chaining with Functions
let user = {

    greet() {
        return "Hello";
    }

};

console.log(user.greet?.());
console.log(user.login?.());

Output

Hello
undefined
3. Nullish Coalescing (??) ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

The ?? operator returns the right-hand value only if the left-hand value is null or undefined.

Example
let name = null;

console.log(name ?? "Guest");

Output

Guest
let city = undefined;

console.log(city ?? "Coimbatore");

Output

Coimbatore
let course = "Java";

console.log(course ?? "React");

Output

Java
Difference Between || and ?? ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Many beginners confuse these operators.

Using ||
let score = 0;

console.log(score || 100);

Output

100

Why?

0 is considered a falsy value.

Using ??
let score = 0;

console.log(score ?? 100);

Output

0

?? treats only null and undefined as missing values.

More Examples
Empty String
let name = "";

console.log(name || "Guest");
console.log(name ?? "Guest");

Output

Guest


(The second output is an empty string.)

Boolean
let isAdmin = false;

console.log(isAdmin || true);
console.log(isAdmin ?? true);

Output

true
false
Comparison Table

| Value | value || "Default" | value ?? "Default" |
|--------|----------------------|----------------------|
| null | Default | Default |
| undefined | Default | Default |
| 0 | Default | 0 |
| false | Default | false |
| "" | Default | "" |

Combining ?. and ??
let student = {
    name: "Priya"
};

let city = student.address?.city ?? "City Not Available";

console.log(city);

Output

City Not Available
Real-World Example – API Response
const user = {
    name: "Priya"
};

console.log(user.address?.city ?? "Unknown City");

Output

Unknown City
Real-World Example – Shopping Website
const product = {
    name: "Laptop"
};

const discount = product.discount ?? 0;

console.log(discount);

Output

0
Common Mistakes
❌ Using || for Numeric Values

Wrong

let price = 0;

console.log(price || 100);

Output

100

Correct

console.log(price ?? 100);

Output

0
❌ Accessing Missing Properties

Wrong

console.log(student.address.city);

Correct

console.log(student.address?.city);
Interview Questions ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
1. What are Default Parameters?

Default parameters assign a default value to a function parameter when no argument is passed.

2. What is Optional Chaining?

Optional chaining (?.) safely accesses nested properties without throwing an error if an intermediate property is null or undefined.

3. What is Nullish Coalescing?

The ?? operator returns the right-hand value only if the left-hand value is null or undefined.

4. Difference between || and ???
|| checks all falsy values (0, false, "", null, undefined, NaN).
?? checks only null and undefined.
